The paper discusses a learning algorithm for robots to adapt to damage, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm involves combining an evolutionary algorithm and Bayesian optimization, which are both commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions increasing the robot's autonomy, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the experiments involve a simulation and a locomotion task, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if visual sensors are used.
